               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18630406-name-540" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18630406-name-540" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18630406-name-540" type="surname" value="CURTIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18630406-name-540" type="given" value="CHRISTOPHER CHAPMAN"></interp>CHRISTOPHER CHAPMAN CURTIS</persName>
                  </hi> I live with my father, who is a baker, at No. 4, Franklin-place, New Cross—on Good Friday afternoon I was at Blackheath, looking at a stall, and felt my watch chain caught—I looked round, and saw the prisoner with my watch in his hand, trying to twist it off the chain—I had my watch before that in my waistcoat pocket—he did not succeed in breaking the chain, and I kept possession of my watch—I and John Jury, who was with me, followed him—he was stopped by a post<lb></lb>man, and I gave him into custody.</p>
